com.jonlatane.composer.music.coverings
Class Clef

java.lang.Object
  com.jonlatane.composer.music.coverings.Clef

public class Clef
extends java.lang.Object

A Clef, assuming that any clef *must* define Middle C/white keys in general as being on either a space or a line, may be represented as an integer. This integer is to be treated as heptatonically. The integer values of each Clef below represent how many steps middle C is above its "normal" position on the treble clef (the first ledger line below the staff).

Author:
Jon Latane

getHeptatonicStepsFromCenter

public  getHeptatonicStepsFromCenter(PitchSet ps)
Returns a pair representing the total span in Heptatonic steps from the center of this Clef. For instance, "A4, C5" on a Treble Clef will return the pair <-1, 1>, because A4 and C5 are respective one step below and above B4, the center of the Treble Clef staff. This requires that the NOTENAMES field of the PitchSet is set.

Parameters:
ps -
Returns:
